The paper deals with the distributional connection between lossy compressed representation of high-dimensional signals and observations under additive white Gaussian noise. This connects to several sub-categories of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper's focus on compression constraints and parameter estimation also suggests these sub-categories.
